<div class="quotetitle">goto80 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />For the C64 there's Hysteria, subsong 3 (Fred Gray 1987) which has a delay of sorts, using PWM. Supercan (Lars Hård 1986) uses delay around 02.20, but it's only one step so it's not that obvious. <br /><br />I'm actually surprised I didn't find more (even with the help of those CSDb-forums), but it's a tricky thing to look for. And yeah, neither of these are very extensive use of delay anyway.<br /><br />But it sure seems like C64 was first. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /><br /></div><br /><br />Good stuff. Y'know I thought of Fred Gray and dug out of few of his tunes but I missed Hysteria.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3896">neilbaldwin</a> — Tue Aug 25, 2009 1:31 pm</p><hr />
