<author><name><![CDATA[ccovell]]></name></author>
<updated>2009-07-14T19:09:15-07:00</updated>
<published>2009-07-14T19:09:15-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5397&amp;p=48875#p48875</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5397&amp;p=48875#p48875"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[History of The Single Voice Echo?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5397&amp;p=48875#p48875"><![CDATA[
This probably isn't single-voice echo, but if you want to hear some games on the NES/Famicom that use echoes as their main "thing", check out many Kemco games (<strong>Bugs Bunny, Shadowgate, Uninvited, Deja Vu</strong>...) as well as <strong>Xexyz</strong> &amp; many compositions by Masuko "Macco" Tsukasa (one of my favourite composers on the PC-Engine), like <strong>Bio Senshi Dan</strong>,  <strong>Rockin' Kats</strong>, and <strong>Megami Tensei II</strong>.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=355">ccovell</a> — Tue Jul 14, 2009 7:09 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
